2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses a relay network, which is a type of network architecture. The paper also proposes a power allocation algorithm, which is relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a power allocation algorithm, which can be seen as a control problem. The paper also deals with the analysis of the statistical characteristics of the received signal, which can be seen as a system identification problem. 
4. cs.COMM (Computer Communications and Networks): The paper discusses a relay network, which is a type of communication network. The paper also proposes a power allocation algorithm, which is relevant to computer communications and networks. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with the analysis of the statistical characteristics of the received signal, which can be relevant to multimedia applications that require reliable transmission of data.
